). MALE. Body 2.11 mm . LFW 1.43 mm .

Metasoma . 1.41 × longer than wide; tergum 1 with ventral region coriaceous, without lap of lateral margin, without lateral pilosity; tergum 2 with dorsal region polished, without lateral pilosity, with ventral region polished; terga 3–6 with dorsal region polished, with ventral region polished; with posterior margin of tergites straight, with sparse setae at posterior margin of terga 2–6 . Hypopygium (
Fig. 58
) wider than long; with hypopygial median stalk undivided; lateral margin parallel, and slightly convex; with posterior margin bilobate with median indentation, with lobate branch.

